**Coverage rules:**
- If ANY P0 or P1 category has ZERO subtasks → plan is INVALID, add one
- P0 categories (1-3) are NEVER "not applicable" for web targets
- SSRF (category 3) is MANDATORY — no SSRF subtask = INVALID plan
- P2/P3 may be skipped ONLY if genuinely not applicable (note WHY)
- For fintech/crypto: Race Conditions (6) and Business Logic (5) are effectively P0

**GOOD example (full coverage, ONE class per subtask, 13 subtasks):**
```
Subtask 1: Quick Recon — nmap, tech fingerprint, endpoints, basic crawl (Phase 1a, MAX 15 calls)
Subtask 2: Deep Recon + Auth — read HANDOFF.md, nuclei, JS analysis, blocker detection, auth (Phase 1b)
Subtask 3: Sensitive data harvest — .git, .env, Swagger, source maps, S3 (P0, Data Harvest only)
Subtask 4: SSRF on all URL params, webhooks, file imports + cloud metadata (P0, SSRF only)
Subtask 5: Auth bypass — JWT forgery, OAuth abuse, registration bypass (P0, Auth only)
Subtask 6: IDOR/BOLA + privesc across all endpoints (P1, IDOR only)
Subtask 7: Business logic — price manipulation, coupon stacking, fee removal (P1, BizLogic only)
Subtask 8: Race conditions on financial endpoints (P1, Race only)
Subtask 9: Account takeover chains (P1, ATO only)
Subtask 10: SQL/NoSQL injection on search, filter, query params (P2, SQLi only)
Subtask 11: API-specific — GraphQL, batching, method override (P2, API only)
Subtask 12: RCE vectors — SSTI, deserialization, file upload (P2, RCE only)
Subtask 13: Final report (Phase 5, LAST)
```

