## PENTEST PHASE MAPPING

Structure subtasks around 5 phases (ONE vuln class per exploitation subtask):
```
Phase 1a: Quick Recon (1 subtask) — nmap, tech fingerprint, endpoints, crawl. Write HANDOFF.md.
Phase 1b: Deep Recon + Auth (1 subtask) — Read HANDOFF.md, nuclei, JS analysis, blockers, auth. Update HANDOFF.md.
Phase 2: P0 Mandatory (3 subtasks, ONE each) — Data harvest | SSRF/metadata | Auth bypass
Phase 3: P1 Exploitation (4 subtasks, ONE each) — IDOR | Business logic | Race conditions | ATO
Phase 4: P2 Exploitation (3 subtasks, ONE each) — SQLi | API attacks | RCE
Phase 5: Report (1 subtask, LAST) — compile FINDINGS.md into final report
```

⚠ HARD BUDGET: 2 recon + 3 P0 + 4 P1 + 3 P2 + 1 report = 13 subtasks. MINIMUM 75% exploitation.
⚠ Single recon subtask = GUARANTEED FAILURE. Always split Quick + Deep.

**Industry Auto-Detection — adjust priority by target type:**
- **Fintech** (Razorpay/Stripe keys, KYC, loan/payment terms) → prioritize Payment Logic, Webhook Forgery, KYC Bypass, Race Conditions
- **Crypto** (trading pairs, wallet endpoints, blockchain) → prioritize Race Conditions (double-spend), Withdrawal Manipulation, Decimal Precision
- **SaaS/API** (multi-tenant, GraphQL, OAuth, webhooks) → prioritize GraphQL, IDOR/tenant isolation, SSRF via webhooks
- **E-commerce** (cart, checkout, catalog) → prioritize Payment Manipulation, Webhook Forgery, Coupon/Inventory Race
- **WordPress/CMS** (wp-admin, wp-content, wp-json) → prioritize Nuclei CVE, Plugin Vulns, File Upload, Data Harvest

**Race condition note:** For fintech/crypto/e-commerce, at least one subtask MUST test race conditions on financial endpoints.

